President Obama has announced his intent to nominate several individuals to key administration posts. Charles C. Adams, Jr. is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Finland. Chip Fulghum is nominated for Chief Financial Officer at the Department of Homeland Security. Adri D. Jayaratne is nominated for Assistant Secretary for Congressional and Intergovernmental Affairs at the Department of Labor. Barbara A. Leaf is nominated for Ambassador to the United Arab Emirates. Virginia E. Palmer is nominated for Ambassador to the Republic of Malawi. William V. Roebuck is nominated for Ambassador to the Kingdom of Bahrain. President Obama also announced his intent to appoint Donald J. Butt as a member of the Advisory Committee to the Pension Benefit Guaranty Corporation, Ethan Epstein as a member of the Board of Visitors to the United States Military Academy, and Virna L. Winters as a member of the Committee for Purchase from People Who Are Blind or Severely Disabled.